Debugging Tip #1: Print things out a lot.
Debugging Tip #2: Start with code that already works.
Debugging Tip #3: If you're not sure what the problem is, divide and conquer.

Debugging Tip #4: Read out your problem and what you want to do.
Even if it's to a rubber duck.
Debugging Tip #5: Plan out your code. Every edit can throw more bugs on the wall.
Debugging Tip #6: Get up and drink some water. Give yourself a break!
Debugging Tip #7: Don't rush to fix your bug. Take your time.
Debugging Tip #8: Name your variables appropriately.
